wikipedia_page.main: Osman Jessop (3 January 1878 – 25 May 1941) was an English cricketer. He played for Gloucestershire between 1901 and 1911.

response: Jessop's father Gilbert Jessop, Sr. played Test cricket for England, as well as first-class cricket for Gloucestershire, Cambridge University and London County. His uncle Osman Jessop also played first-class cricket for Gloucestershire.
